title: Independent candidate Bilal wins PS-109 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Bilal Hussain Khan Jadoon has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-109 Karachi South-VI constituency by securing 27,885 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muhammad Zakar Mehnati of Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan who bagged 12,825 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 31.27 per cent in the constituency.
